This implementation:

1. Adds a toggle button to switch between "Online Users" and "All Users" views
2. Maintains a list of all users and a set of online user IDs
3. Updates the user list renderer to show online/offline status
4. Modifies the user list update handlers to track online status
5. Adds methods to load all users from the database (simulated for now)

The key features are:

1. **Toggle Button**: Users can switch between viewing only online users or all users
2. **Online Status Indicator**: Each user in the list has a status indicator showing if they're online or offline
3. **User Management**: The application tracks all users and their online status
4. **Real-time Updates**: The user list updates in real-time as users join or leave

This implementation provides a more comprehensive user management system, allowing users to see who's online and who's offline, and to initiate chats with any user regardless of their online status (though messages to offline users would be delivered when they come online).
